8-1 General.

a. A multiple-address letter is used when the originator determines that correspondence with the same subject and content must be dispatched to more than one activity or individual within the Department of the Navy. The letter may also be used to correspond with commands of other services, other Government agencies, and the general public when the conditions in paragraph 8-1a apply and military and Government standards make its use feasible. A multiple-address letter is prepared based on the standard letter format detailed in chapter 7, with the modifications described herein.

b. Situations that do not warrant preparation of a multiple-address letter are:
(1) When separate letters are prepared anyway (e.g., different enclosures are required for different addressees);
(2) Several addressees are at different levels in the chain of command (e.g., some To, some Via);
(3) When a letter requires individual signature of the originator for each addressee.
